org.freezedry.persistence.builders

Class MapNodeBuilder

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.freezedry.persistence.builders.AbstractNodeBuilder
      • org.freezedry.persistence.builders.MapNodeBuilder
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    NodeBuilder, Copyable<NodeBuilder>

    public class MapNodeBuilder
extends AbstractNodeBuilder
    Handles the persistence and serialization of Map objects. When use for serialization (i.e. typically when maps are root objects it is for serialization), then applies a key- and value-prefix to the key's and value's respectively.

      • getKeyValueNames

        private Pair<java.lang.String,java.lang.String> getKeyValueNames(java.lang.Class<?> containingClass,
                                                       InfoNode node)
        Returns the key and value names for the Map. These are either default values, or, if the field has a PersistMap annotation, it may have overridden either the key or value name. For example, suppose the user has annotated the field with @PersistMap(entryPersistName="client",keyPersistName="endPoint",valuePersistName="weight"). Then the info node of the children would contain "endpoint" instead of the expected "Key" for the key name, and "weight" instead of the expected "Value" for the value. And the we need to know that so we can deal with it.
        Parameters:
        containingClass - The Class containing the field represented by the specified node
        node - The node representing the field
        Returns:
        The key and value names associated with the Map

      • getCopy

        public NodeBuilder getCopy()
        Description copied from interface: Copyable
        Creates and returns a copy of the object x that meets the following criteria
        1. The expressions x.getCopy() != x evaluates as true
        2. The expressions x.getCopy().equals( x ) evaluates as true
        3. The expressions x.getCopy().getClass() == x.getClass() evaluates as true
        Returns:
        a copy of the object that meets the above criteria
